gomodel:SYNGO_217  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using immuno-EM on rat hippoacampal tissue this paper demonstrates that the transmembrane receptor mGluR5 is localized at the periphery of the PSD.\n\n9/3/2017 Pim:\n-Fig 6 show quantitative support for postsynaptic membrane localizition just **outside** of the PSD membrane (so not **inside** the PSD membrane), this choice is bit arbitatry I guess. But I chosse to follow the data in figure 6.\n-Since Fig.6. is on CA1 area of hippocampus I added this info to the synapse type info.\n-\"integral component\" rerived from TM domains of GRM5.. Experimental description: from M&M: \"[...] adult female Wistar rats (200-250 g) were deeply anaesthetized [...]\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_217" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

